  - 464
By: Hakuin
---
In this final world age, which is the age of dissolutions, ... the wondrous law
of the one mind is being discarded everywhere, and each individual is now
thinking just as he individually wishes to think. Sometimes it seems as if the
real desire to know the truth is there -- almost as it were by chance, but it
soon turns out to be nothing but a sort of philosophical discussion or an
elegant fashion of talk.
